# TodoMVC Architecture Plan

## Overview
Full-stack TodoMVC: Rust Axum backend + Leptos WASM frontend, SQLite storage.

## Workspace Structure
```
Cargo.toml              # workspace: members = ["backend", "frontend"]
backend/
  Cargo.toml            # axum, tokio, serde, serde_json, rusqlite, uuid, tower-http
  src/
    main.rs             # server startup, router assembly, static file serving
    db.rs               # SQLite init, migrations, connection pool
    models.rs           # Todo struct (id, title, completed, order) + serde
    repo.rs             # CRUD: list_all, create, get_by_id, update, delete, delete_completed, toggle_all
    routes.rs           # Axum handlers: GET/POST/PATCH/DELETE /api/todos/*
  tests/
    api_tests.rs        # integration tests against real HTTP server
frontend/
  Cargo.toml            # leptos, gloo-net, serde, wasm-bindgen
  Trunk.toml            # build config, proxy to backend in dev
  index.html            # entry point, loads todomvc-app-css
  src/
    main.rs             # mount App component
    app.rs              # TodoApp root: fetches todos, composes children
    api.rs              # HTTP client functions (gloo-net)
    models.rs           # Shared Todo type (mirrors backend)
    router.rs           # Hash-based routing (#/, #/active, #/completed)
    components/
      mod.rs
      header.rs         # TodoHeader: input + create
      todo_item.rs      # TodoItem: display, toggle, delete, inline edit
      todo_list.rs      # TodoList: renders items, toggle-all
      footer.rs         # TodoFooter: count, filters, clear completed
  src/tests/            # wasm-bindgen-test unit tests
Makefile                # dev/build scripts (trunk build, cargo run)
.github/workflows/ci.yml
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
README.md
```

## Issue Dependency Graph
```
Phase 1 - Foundation:
  #1 Cargo workspace + backend crate
  #2 Leptos frontend crate + Trunk

Phase 2 - Backend Core (depends on #1):
  #3 Static file serving + CSS (depends on #1, #2)
  #4 CI pipeline (depends on #1, #2)
  #5 SQLite setup (depends on #1)
  #6 Data model + repo (depends on #5)
  #7 REST API endpoints (depends on #6)
  #8 API integration tests (depends on #7)

Phase 3 - Frontend Core (depends on #7):
  #9  API client module (depends on #7)
  #10 TodoHeader (depends on #9)
  #11 TodoItem (depends on #9)
  #12 TodoList + toggle-all (depends on #11)
  #13 Inline editing (depends on #11)
  #14 Hash-based routing (depends on #12)

Phase 4 - Assembly:
  #15 TodoFooter (depends on #14)
  #16 TodoApp root (depends on #10, #12, #15)
  #17 Frontend tests (depends on #16)
  #18 Dockerfile (depends on #16)
  #19 README
```

## Key Design Decisions
- **rusqlite** (not sqlx): simpler, no async complexity for SQLite, no compile-time query checking needed
- **gloo-net** for frontend HTTP: standard WASM HTTP client
- **UUID strings** for todo IDs: avoids integer conflicts, matches TodoMVC spec
- **tower-http** ServeDir for static files: serves Trunk's dist/ output
- **Shared types**: backend models.rs and frontend models.rs mirror each other (no shared crate to keep workspace simple)
- **Hash routing**: client-side only via gloo-utils or manual window().location().hash()
- **Single binary deployment**: Dockerfile embeds dist/ assets into the container alongside the backend binary
